# User Profile Menu Implementation Plan

## Goal
Implement a small, responsive pop-up menu that appears when a user clicks on their profile section in the dashboard sidebar. This menu will display their Name and Email (read-only) and a clickable "Configurações" (Settings) option, aligning with the premium UI expectations.

## Proposed Changes

### [src/app/dashboard/dashboard-client.tsx](file:///c:/Users/igor_/.gemini/antigravity/playground/turatuno/turatuno-web/src/app/dashboard/dashboard-client.tsx) and [src/app/dashboard/relatorios/reports-client.tsx](file:///c:/Users/igor_/.gemini/antigravity/playground/turatuno/turatuno-web/src/app/dashboard/relatorios/reports-client.tsx)
- **[MODIFY] state variables**: Add a new state `showProfileMenu` to toggle the visibility of the popup menu.
- **[MODIFY] user section**: Wrap the profile box with a conditional rendering block for the popup menu. The menu will stop event propagation so clicking inside it doesn't close the menu, but clicking outside will.
- **[MODIFY] click handler**: Change the current `onClick` that sets `profileOpen` (which opens a full modal) to toggle `showProfileMenu` instead. Move the `setProfileOpen` logic into the "Configurações" button within the new menu.

### [src/app/dashboard/dashboard.module.css](file:///c:/Users/igor_/.gemini/antigravity/playground/turatuno/turatuno-web/src/app/dashboard/dashboard.module.css) and [src/app/dashboard/relatorios/relatorios.module.css](file:///c:/Users/igor_/.gemini/antigravity/playground/turatuno/turatuno-web/src/app/dashboard/relatorios/relatorios.module.css)
- **[MODIFY] popup menu styles**: Add CSS classes for `.profileMenu`, `.profileMenuHeader`, `.profileMenuEmail`, `.profileMenuItem` to style the floating menu card with a premium glassmorphic or solid surface look, complete with shadows and rounded corners.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
* None available for this specific UI component.

### Manual Verification
1. Open the dashboard.
2. Click on the user profile section at the bottom of the sidebar.
3. Verify that a small menu pops up.
4. Verify the menu displays the user's Name and Email.
5. Verify the menu has a clickable "Configurações" option.
6. Click "Configurações" and visually confirm that it opens the user profile editing modal.
7. Click outside the menu to verify it closes.
